title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\ModelEvaluation
name: ModelEvaluation
description:
A collection of metrics calculated by comparing Model's predictions on all of the test data against annotations from the test data.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.ModelEvaluation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data.data_item_schema_uri
params.description: Points to a YAML file stored on Google Cloud Storage describing [EvaluatedDataItemView.data_item_payload][] and [EvaluatedAnnotation.data_item_payload][]. The schema is defined as an OpenAPI 3.0.2 Schema Object. This field is not populated if there are neither EvaluatedDataItemViews nor EvaluatedAnnotations under this ModelEvaluation.

params.name: data.annotation_schema_uri
params.description: Points to a YAML file stored on Google Cloud Storage describing [EvaluatedDataItemView.predictions][], [EvaluatedDataItemView.ground_truths][], [EvaluatedAnnotation.predictions][], and [EvaluatedAnnotation.ground_truths][]. The schema is defined as an OpenAPI 3.0.2 Schema Object. This field is not populated if there are neither EvaluatedDataItemViews nor EvaluatedAnnotations under this ModelEvaluation.

params.name: data.model_explanation
params.description: Aggregated explanation metrics for the Model's prediction output over the data this ModelEvaluation uses. This field is populated only if the Model is evaluated with explanations, and only for AutoML tabular Models.

params.name: data.explanation_specs
params.description: Describes the values of [ExplanationSpec][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.ExplanationSpec] that are used for explaining the predicted values on the evaluated data.

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: The metadata of the ModelEvaluation. For the ModelEvaluation uploaded from Managed Pipeline, metadata contains a structured value with keys of "pipeline_job_id", "evaluation_dataset_type", "evaluation_dataset_path".
